fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
In some language of modular systems, we say such a system is compositional if it supports the horizontal and vertical composition operators, and that these operators make the modular system a symmetric monoidal category.

Module-module horizontal composition.
               \frac {           M : \text {Mod}(E_L, F_L) \quad            N : \text {Mod}(E_R, F_R)         }{           M \otimes  N : \text {Mod}(E_L + E_R, F_L + F_R)         }       

Spec-spec horizontal composition.
               \frac {           V : \text {Spec}(L) \quad            W : \text {Spec}(R)         }{           V \otimes  W : \text {Spec}(L + R)         }       

Module-module vertical composition.
               \frac {           M : \text {Mod}(E, F) \quad            N : \text {Mod}(F, G)         }{           M \rhd  N : \text {Mod}(E, G)         }       

Spec-module vertical composition.
               \frac {           V : \text {Spec}(E) \quad            M : \text {Mod}(E, F)         }{           V \rhd  M : \text {Mod}(E, G)         }
